rstanarm Examples

Jim Albert

7/10/2017

Linear Regression Problem

Fitting simple linear regression model for the cars dataset.

\[ y_i \sim N(a + b x_i, \sigma) \] (Priors will be described below.)

Hamiltonian Sampling

Load the rstanarm package:

library(rstanarm)

Set some parameters of MCMC algorithms.

ITER <- 1000L
CHAINS <- 2L
CORES <- 2L
SEED <- 12345

Function stan_glm is the Bayesian equivalent to the glm function.

fit <- stan_glm(dist ~ speed, data = cars,
               family = gaussian(link = "identity"), 
                  chains = CHAINS, cores = CORES, 
               seed = SEED, iter = ITER)

The prior_summary function states the default priors in the Bayesian model.

prior_summary(fit)
## Priors for model 'fit' 
## ------
## Intercept (after predictors centered)
##  ~ normal(location = 0, scale = 10)
##      **adjusted scale = 257.69
## 
## Coefficients
##  ~ normal(location = 0, scale = 2.5)
##      **adjusted scale = 12.18
## 
## Auxiliary (sigma)
##  ~ half-cauchy(location = 0, scale = 5)
##      **adjusted scale = 128.85
## ------
## See help('prior_summary.stanreg') for more details

A Few MCMC Diagnostics and Summaries

Here are several plots from the bayesplot function.

draws <- as.array(fit)
library(bayesplot)
mcmc_hist_by_chain(draws, pars = c("speed", "sigma"))

mcmc_trace(draws)
